10/02/2008
MUNICH, Germany -- NATO Secretary-General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer said on Saturday (February 9th) that NATO is ready to be a real partner to Serbia.
Speaking at an international security conference in Munich, de hoop Scheffer said NATO believes Kosovo should be a stable region, where Albanian and Serbs could leave peacefully together.
He also encouraged membership aspirants Macedonia, Croatia and Albania, saying he hopes all three will be invited to join the Alliance at its next summit in April.
(A1, Makfax, ITAR-TASS, MIA, AFP - 09/02/08)
